parameters: \N<Seno>Get it together there. Let's start over from the beginning.

\N<Seno>Haha, that's the spirit. You've got a big frame, so make
sure you use it properly.

\N<Seno>There have been reports of suspicious movements from the
Ryuda faction. In other words, it wouldn't be strange if we
ended up in battle at any time. Everyone needs to be on
their toes.

\N<Orugi>I've finished selecting the personnel for that strategy.
Make sure to check it out.
\N<Deli>No, not yet...! Just a little longer... please!

\N<Orugi>Why the rush? If you get injured before the operation, it'll
all be for naught.

\N<Orugi>Are you anxious about participating in the operation?
Thinking you're not up to the task. Worried you might not
make it back alive.

\N<Deli>To say I'm not scared of dying... would be a lie. But... I
understand that this is an honorable thing to do.
\N<Deli>The vice-captain has fired me up about it too.

\N<Deli>That's why... that's why I can do my best. Even if fear
makes my legs tremble... I'll endure it.

\N<Deli>I understand that people have their strengths and
weaknesses. No matter how much I train, I know I'll never
catch up to the captain or the vice-captain.
\N<Deli>But still... I want to become stronger.

\N<Deli>Of course... as a man living in this country, as a
soldier...

\N<Deli>And then... to become strong enough to protect the woman I
have feelings for.

\N<Orugi>...I see. Then I won't go easy on you. Come, let me be your
opponent for a while longer.

\N<Seno>Reckless... I understand the sentiment, but you're too
hasty, just like he said.

\N<Seno>Yeah. You can't just skip steps and expect to become strong
so easily, right? At this rate, it's your body that's going
to break down first.

\N<Seno>Really now... Can you stand? Here, grab on. I'll lend you my
shoulder back to the barracks.
\N<Deli>Am I... am I not good enough?! Do you dislike me?!

\N<Seno>Calm down a bit... It's not about that. All my subordinates
are dear to me and precious, of course.

\N<Seno>You understand, right? It's not about that. Please be
reasonable.
\N<Seno>Are you into women who spread their legs for just anyone?

\N<Seno>I have a husband. To acquiesce to your request would mean
just that.

\N<Deli>The captain is with the vice-captain... I know that. But...
but still, I want you...

\N<Deli>I-I'm a man... and a soldier at that! So... I'm not...
scared...!

\N<Seno>But you're trembling. Could it be that you're flustered
because you were chosen for that particular mission?

\N<Seno>You don't need to force yourself to act tough, saying you're
a man or a soldier. That's something for those who can
actually do it.

\N<Seno>So there's no need to be ashamed of being scared. A soldier
who doesn't know fear is nothing more than a foolhardy
braggart.

\N<Seno>...You're in love with me, aren't you? If so, did touching
the woman you like calm you down a bit?

\N<Seno>If your head has cooled off, let's leave it at that. If it's
now, I'll just consider it a touch on the butt during
training.

\N<Seno>It's alright... It happens to everyone. You were just
flustered. A momentary lapse, that's all.

\N<Seno>More importantly... remember our promise? Keep the condition
of my butt a secret from everyone.
